The colonia's defense committee drills what it hopes never to use and uses more than it hoped: the barricade plan, the whistle relay, the women's line that meets the granaderos first because even this state hesitates one extra minute before clubbing grandmothers on camera. That minute, multiplied by organization, is the whole science of not being evicted — and whatever else moves through the colonia moves behind it.
